summary: I have this weird Pre-cybernetics-Grievous headcanon where Qymaen had this wife, his very first wife, who not many people knew...
body: I have this weird Pre-cybernetics-Grievous headcanon where Qymaen had this wife, his very first wife, who not many people knew about. She was good friends, very very close friends… bordering romantic nature, with Ronderu and they’d known each other long before Qymaen even came into the picture. I might even go so far as to say they grew up together and only she really knows Ronderu’s true origins. I like to think that she met Qymaen, along side Ronderu, in the Kunbal Jungal when the infamous kaleesh general sought to find the origin of his fabled dream. I like to think that obviously since she wasn’t very well known and is never mentioned as being involved with the Huk War, she fought alongside her husband and best friend anonymously or very scarcely. When Ronderu is killed, she goes into a very deep depression and enters a near vegetative state, symbolically dying with her late friend. This is what really sends Qymaen over the edge who was also already grieving the loss of his most trusted companion. But long after Ronderu and Qymaen, now Grievous, are dead, she realizes that she must become strong and stands up for Kalee and her people in their place, becoming the unknown kaleesh woman who defends her people today.

summary: Someone also had a remote controlled R2D2 out trick-or-treating and were allowing all the kids (and some adults) to take...
caption:
Someone also had a remote controlled R2D2 out trick-or-treating and were allowing all the kids (and some adults) to take pictures with it.

I tried to capture of photo of it without too much of a crowd but it was fairly difficult… This ended up being the best picture of the ones I managed to take.
My brother is a huge Star Wars fan and sadly had to miss out on trick-or-treating this year due to his college classes  :(  so I wanted to show him this.


Photo taken on Oct 30, 2018

blog.name: minerfromtarn
blog.title: Towards Peace
blog.description:
"Be he foe or friend, be he foul or clean,

brood of Morgoth or bright Vala,

Elda or Maia or Aftercomer,

Man yet unborn upon Middle-earth,

neither law, nor love, nor league of swords,

dread nor danger, not Doom itself,

shall defend him from Fëanor, and Fëanor's kin,

whoso hideth or hoardeth, or in hand taketh,

finding keepeth or afar casteth

a Silmaril. This swear we all:

death we will deal him ere Day's ending,

woe unto world's end! Our word hear thou,

Eru Allfather! To the everlasting

Darkness doom us if our deed faileth.

On the holy mountain hear in witness

and our vow remember, Manwë and Varda!"

Bi/nonbinary, any pronoun works, Decepticon, Converting to Judaism
